<span id="iv.iv.viii.xxix"></span>

#### <span id="iv.iv.viii.xxix-p0.1"></span>Chapter XXIX.

<span id="iv.iv.viii.xxix-p1"></span>An objection, asking why those who
are tormented by unclean spirits are separated from the Lord’s
communion.

<span id="iv.iv.viii.xxix-p2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="iv.iv.viii.xxix-p2.1"></span>Germanus</span>:  And how is it that we
see them not only scorned and shunned by everybody, but actually always
kept away from the Lord’s communion in our provinces, in accordance with
these words of the gospel: “Give not that which is holy to the dogs,
neither cast your pearls before swine;” <span
id="fr_1497"></span>[1498](#fn_1497.md) while you tell us that somehow we
ought to hold that the humiliation of this temptation is brought upon
them with a view to their purification and profit?

